This paper deals with the problem of cross-modal face verification and recognition using deep learning networks. The paper focuses on the computer vision aspect of the problem, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with multimodal learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves knowledge transfer, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
